line_2: Her bread will ay be baken.

line_1: Of Gods, as well as Men, mistaken.
line_2: By Human Force could ne'er be shaken:

line_1: May find himself in time mistaken.
line_2: Yet he, who thinks the church unshaken,

line_1: But troth he'll find himsel mista'en, —
line_2: THE auld carle wad tak me fain,

line_1: How often, pray, are we mistaken,
line_2: When we conclude we're really waking?

line_1: To catch the fore — but they're mistaken —
line_2: When they lie down they're overtaken.
